        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Fibrous Skeleton of the Heart: Anatomic Overview and Evaluation of Pathologic Conditions with CT and MR Imaging" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Farhood  Saremi" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Damián  Sánchez-Quintana" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Shumpei  Mori" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Horia  Muresian" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Diane                            E.  Spicer" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Cameron  Hassani" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Robert                            H.  Anderson" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="This review provides a comprehensive overview of the anatomy of the fibrous skeleton of the heart and its related components, supported by relevant images of anatomy and pathologic processes." /><meta name="Description" content="This review provides a comprehensive overview of the anatomy of the fibrous skeleton of the heart and its related components, supported by relevant images of anatomy and pathologic processes." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The fibrous skeleton is concentrated at the base of the ventricular mass. It provides electrical insulation at the atrioventricular level and fibrous continuity for the leaflets of the mitral, aort..." /><meta name="Description" content="The fibrous skeleton is concentrated at the base of the ventricular mass. It provides electrical insulation at the atrioventricular level and fibrous continuity for the leaflets of the mitral, aort..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content=" Radiological Society of North America " /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2017-08-18" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="170004" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content=